100 is probably the least useful. I'd say drop it, and you can always take it later in summer or something.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I'd say it depends on what you're trying to do later. Are you planning on taking 162 or one of the 160's in the future? If so you need 61c. But if you aren't, then 61c could be easily pushed off to clear space. If you're already doing research, chances are you're gonna pick up the Data 100 techniques naturally tbh. For me, 61c was definitely a higher workload.
100 is probably the least useful. I'd say drop it, and you can always take it later in summer or something.

Hi, I'm a junior in CS and I'm currently taking 170, 61C, and Data 100, and I just committed to 3 units (8-11 hours/week) of research in data engineering/ML as well. The workload has already been a lot without research + recruiting (mostly from 61C) and it's been hard to stay on track due to the online format. I'm trying to get strong grades to go to grad school so I'd like to drop one of the three and add a breadth. 

Does anyone have recommendations for which class of the three I should drop? I'm thinking to stay in 170 for sure for SWE interviews. Thanks!
history.subject: Junior CS Advice- What class to drop?
